To recognise the contribution of the informal sector of the Lagos economy, which accounts for 94 percent of new jobs in the state, a group, StartUp & FinishRich Impact Concept, will in June, 2022, honour artisans and tradesman in the state. The award ceremony scheduled for Agege Stadium coincides with the 25th anniversary of the Lagos State Council of Tradesmen & Artisans (LASCOTA).   Kidnappers knelt before me for prayers, says freed pastor     Policeman, three others killed in Anambra      10 die, 23 rescued in Lagos building collapse   It is a special recognition for diverse categories of deserving artisans and tradesmen who have distinguished themselves in their various trades in both the public and private sectors. “Over the years, artisans and tradesmen have been looked down on and treated with disdain…To change this perception and reconstruct their social identity, their values must be acknowledged, recognised, and celebrated,” coordinator of the event, Rabiu Adewunmi Momoh, said.